description: Using account ID, profile ID, fetch the balance records
Using account ID, profile ID, query the balance records

A balance record reflects either funds being added or deducted from a Wix Payments balance.
This can result from a charge, refund, chargeback, chargeback or refund reversal, or a reserve.
Note: In certain cases Balance Record can be "virtual" - it's not physically created yet, but will be created at some point of time in future.
Such records have no "id" and "applied_date"

members.name: amount
members.doc: This corresponds with the amount of the balance record.

members.name: fee
members.doc: This reflects the fee that Wix Payments collects from each balance record.

members.name: net
members.doc: This reflects the balance net of fees.

members.name: payoutAvailabilityDate
members.doc: Date when balance record is available for payout.

members.name: profileId
members.doc: Account profile balance record belongs to.

description:
Money.
Default format to use. Sufficiently compliant with majority of standards: w3c, ISO 4217, ISO 20022, ISO 8583:2003.

members.name: currency
members.doc: Currency code. Must be valid ISO 4217 currency code (e.g., USD).

members.name: value
members.doc: Monetary amount. Decimal string with a period as a decimal separator (e.g., 3.99). Optionally, a single (-), to indicate that the amount is negative.

members.name: offset
members.doc: Number of items to skip in the current sort order.

members.name: count
members.doc: Number of items returned in the response.

members.name: tooManyToCount
members.doc: Flag that indicates the server failed to calculate the `total` field.

members.name: total
members.doc: Total number of items that match the query.

members.name: _createdDate
members.doc:
The date when balance record was paid out.
This only applies to payouts that have already occurred and not those that are scheduled.

members.name: fields
members.doc: Array of projected fields. A list of specific field names to return. If `fieldsets` are also specified, the union of `fieldsets` and `fields` is returned.

members.name: fieldsets
members.doc: Array of named, predefined sets of projected fields. A array of predefined named sets of fields to be returned. Specifying multiple `fieldsets` will return the union of fields from all sets. If `fields` are also specified, the union of `fieldsets` and `fields` is returned.
